                             Spacers Dare  The game of Spacer's Dare is played with two players (you and this clunkyold gambling computer sitting here in the corner of the Spacers Hangout)and a pair of dice.  There are up to *CLICK* *BUZZ* ten rounds in the gamewith each round consisting of one turn for each player.  Players add *POP**DING* the score they acquire in each round and the player with the highestscore after the selected number of rounds is the *BUZZ* winner.  On each turn the player may roll the dice any number of times.  Here's thecatch though: IF ANY OF THE ROLLS IS EQUAL TO THE FIRST ROLL THEN THATTURN IS OVER AND HIS SCORE FOR THAT ROUND IS ZERO.  After each *CLICK* rollthat does not equal that first roll, the player can decide whether to *POP**SMOKE* roll again or stop and keep the number of credits obtained.  The multiplier is a factor (1-3) that is used to determine your finalscore. If you win, the computer's score is deducted from your *BUZZ* *CLICK*score and the result is multiplied by the multiplier. If you lose, your scoreis *R-R-R-POP* subtracted from the computers and the difference is multipliedby the multiplier. Your final score is what you win or lose in credits.-----------------------------------------------------------------------------    Spacers Dare & Dox written and generously contributed to Spacer Quest   by IRON BROW - 8/12/90 - Sysop - Mile High Apple Pie BBS - 719-632-9126-----------------------------------------------------------------------------